%h1= title("CafeCar — live demo")

= Alert :info, "Live demo — the data resets periodically, so click around freely. You can't break anything."

%p
  Everything under
  %code /admin
  is rendered by
  %strong CafeCar
  straight from plain Rails models — index, show, new, edit, filtering,
  sorting, and pagination — with no hand-written view code. This dummy app
  defines the models; CafeCar renders the whole admin.

- if current_user
  %p= "Signed in as #{current_user.name} — the demo now sends this user to PostHog."
  %p= Button "Continue to the admin →", :primary, href: "/admin/clients"
- else
  -# Sign in as the seeded demo account through the real session flow, so the
  -# demo has a persistent current_user (see User::DEMO_*).
  %p= button_to "Enter the demo →", session_path, class: "Button Button-primary",
        params: { session: { email: User::DEMO_EMAIL, password: User::DEMO_PASSWORD } }

%p
  Or jump to a resource:
  = link_to "clients", "/admin/clients"
  ·
  = link_to "invoices", "/admin/invoices"
  ·
  = link_to "articles", "/admin/articles"
  ·
  = link_to "users", "/admin/users"
  ·
  = link_to "notes", "/admin/notes"

%p
  = link_to "CafeCar on GitHub", "https://github.com/craft-concept/cafe_car"
